sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2027055
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence codes for a cis-prenyltransferase responsible for polymerization of IPP and DMAPP into polyisoprene compounds. This sequence is from the rubber tree, Hevea brasiliensis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Gordon Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Sequence was sourced from Asawatreratanakul K, Zhang YW, Wititsuwannakul D, et al. Molecular cloning, expression and characterization of cDNA encoding cis-prenyltransferases from Hevea brasiliensis. A key factor participating in natural rubber biosynthesis. Eur J Biochem. 2003;270(23):4671-80. (http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/AB064661?report=GenBank)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence has been acquired from H. brasiliensis and codon optimized for transfection into E. coli. No other modifications have been made to the sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence contains the Hevea brasiliensis??HRT1??mRNA for cis-prenyltransferase, complete cds. The sequence has been codon optimized for expression in E. coli. HRT1 is a cis-prenyltransferase and is responsible for initialization and elongation of polyisoprene polymers. It takes in IPP or DMAPP and polymerizes it to a polyisoprene chain.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2027053
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence contains the gene for a small rubber particle protein (SRPP) from the rubber tree Hevea brasiliensis. This coenzyme serves as an activator for rubber transferases/prenyltransferases in H. brasiliensis. This protein is involved in rubber elongation. Characteristics: ??? 612bp ORF ??? 63-bp 59-UTR ??? 181-bp 39-UTR ??? 18bp poly A tail ??? Localized in the cytoplasm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Gordon Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Sequence was sourced from Oh SK, Kang H, Shin DH, et al. Isolation, characterization, and functional analysis of a novel cDNA clone encoding a small rubber particle protein from Hevea brasiliensis. J Biol Chem. 1999;274(24):17132-8. (http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/AF051317)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
This sequence has been codon optimized for transfection into E. coli. Mutation A486T was induced to remove a restriction site.
A FLAG-Lumio tag can be appended to the sequence to allow for visualization and/or purification.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
